I need to calculate the Gross Profit Margin based on the given income statement.

The Gross Profit Margin is calculated as:
Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%

Looking at the income statement:
- Gross Profit = $1,622,011.03
- Total Revenue = $2,637,011.03

Now I'll calculate the Gross Profit Margin:
Gross Profit Margin = ($1,622,011.03 / $2,637,011.03) × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = 0.6151 × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = 61.51%
